sports_Table.detail: Like so many of its characters, Barry drew the short end of the stick. Throughout its fourth and final season, on every Sunday night, Bill Hader's labor of love had to follow Succession. All too often, the who will be the CEO?! noise drowned out the downright extraordinary things that happened in Barry—especially in its last few episodes. Mainly? Emmy-worthy performances from the likes of Sarah Goldberg and Anthony Carrigan, Hader's emergence as a great director, and a fitting, yet divisive finale. But Barry should—and will, I hope—be forever canonized in the HBO Hall of Fame.—B.L
